//ACROSDK_SOURCE_TREE_ROOT is a common environment variable used to tell all the .xcconfig files where the root
//of our source tree is -- currently the same directory as the project file,
//Plugin Support/Samples/Project_Name/mac

ACROSDK_SOURCE_TREE_ROOT = $(SRCROOT)

// Xcode 3: SRCROOT must be explicitly defined in the Project Inspector General tab
// or the project will ask to set it when opening


//ACROBAT_PLUGINS_FOLDER is another environment variable used to tell the release target 
//build script where the Acrobat plug-ins directory is located. Currently set to the 
//Acrobat Professional default install location in Applications

ACROBAT_PLUGINS_FOLDER = /Applications/Adobe Acrobat Next Pro/Adobe Acrobat Pro.app/Contents/Plug-ins




